{"elements":[{"isDeleted":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"sY2ZeG4sSRdXORaI8dgMU","strokeWidth":2,"seed":1735087663,"roughness":1,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772622641651,"text":"Search","locked":false,"version":9,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"aL","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Search","height":25,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":2073063364,"lineHeight":1.25,"fontFamily":8,"textAlign":"left","frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"angle":0,"x":681,"y":145,"width":66},{"isDeleted":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"alfbCA4hjEExwBv2aRQnG","strokeWidth":2,"seed":1801467759,"roughness":1,"fontSize":15.789253050920038,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772622641651,"text":"Crawling and parsing are the first two stages of a web search engine's data ingestion pipeline. \nThe **crawling flow** discovers and downloads web pages, while the **parsing flow** extracts and cleans the content for the next stages.\n\n---\n\n### **Crawling Flow**\n\nThe crawling process begins with a set of **seed URLs** stored in a queue. \nA **URL Manager service** pushes these URLs to a **distributed message queue** (like Kafka). \n\n1.  **Crawler Workers** consume messages from the queue.\n2.  Each worker performs a **DNS lookup** to resolve the domain to an IP address.\n3.  It then fetches the site's **`robots.txt`** file to check for crawl rules and delays.\n4.  The worker makes an **HTTP request** to download the raw HTML content.\n5.  The raw HTML is saved to **Object Storage** (e.g., S3), and a `crawl.raw` event is published to a message queue,\n    carrying only the storage location (e.g., an S3 key). This decouples the crawling from the parsing stage.\n\n---\n\n### **Parsing Flow**\n\nAfter the raw data is stored, the parsing process begins.\n\n1.  A **Parsing Worker** consumes the `crawl.raw` event from the queue.\n2.  It retrieves the raw HTML from Object Storage.\n3.  The parser uses an **HTML parsing library** to build a **Document Object Model (DOM)** tree.\n4.  It extracts two key types of data:\n    * **Content:** The visible text, titles, and metadata are extracted and cleaned.\n    * **Links:** New URLs are found from `<a>` tags and are sent back to the URL Manager to be added to the crawl queue for future crawling.\n5.  The cleaned content is stored in a **Document Store** (a database), and a `crawl.parsed` event is published to a message queue. \n    This event contains the **document ID**, signaling to the next stage (the indexer) that a new document is ready for processing.","locked":false,"version":96,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"aM","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Crawling and parsing are the first two stages of a web search engine's data ingestion pipeline. \nThe **crawling flow** discovers and downloads web pages, while the **parsing flow** extracts and cleans the content for the next stages.\n\n---\n\n### **Crawling Flow**\n\nThe crawling process begins with a set of **seed URLs** stored in a queue. \nA **URL Manager service** pushes these URLs to a **distributed message queue** (like Kafka). \n\n1.  **Crawler Workers** consume messages from the queue.\n2.  Each worker performs a **DNS lookup** to resolve the domain to an IP address.\n3.  It then fetches the site's **`robots.txt`** file to check for crawl rules and delays.\n4.  The worker makes an **HTTP request** to download the raw HTML content.\n5.  The raw HTML is saved to **Object Storage** (e.g., S3), and a `crawl.raw` event is published to a message queue,\n    carrying only the storage location (e.g., an S3 key). This decouples the crawling from the parsing stage.\n\n---\n\n### **Parsing Flow**\n\nAfter the raw data is stored, the parsing process begins.\n\n1.  A **Parsing Worker** consumes the `crawl.raw` event from the queue.\n2.  It retrieves the raw HTML from Object Storage.\n3.  The parser uses an **HTML parsing library** to build a **Document Object Model (DOM)** tree.\n4.  It extracts two key types of data:\n    * **Content:** The visible text, titles, and metadata are extracted and cleaned.\n    * **Links:** New URLs are found from `<a>` tags and are sent back to the URL Manager to be added to the crawl queue for future crawling.\n5.  The cleaned content is stored in a **Document Store** (a database), and a `crawl.parsed` event is published to a message queue. \n    This event contains the **document ID**, signaling to the next stage (the indexer) that a new document is ready for processing.","height":611.83355572315361,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":398614140,"lineHeight":1.25,"fontFamily":8,"textAlign":"left","frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"angle":0,"x":302,"y":290,"width":1215.7724849208453},{"isDeleted":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"9VutiYHHSFxqM0hhVVTZo","strokeWidth":2,"seed":1755104847,"roughness":1,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772622641651,"text":"### Indexing Flow\n\n- Index service consumes “crawl.parsed” events from the message queue.\n  {url, documentId}\n\n- The indexer retrieves the document content from the database.\n- It then breaks the content down into tokens (individual words).\n- Removes punctuations. Replaces & with “and” etc.\n- Converts all tokens\/words into lowercase.\n- Removes stop words such as “the”, “a”, “is”, “and”.\n- The reduces tokens into root forms. Knowns as Stemming\/Lemmatization.\n  For example\n    running, ran, runs -> run\n\n- Then it creates a map of word to freq and positions in local.\n  { \n    run: freq=3, positions=[11,33,45],\n    slow: freq=1, positions=[12],\n  }\n- Then it updates this document frequences in the index.\n   “run” -> {\n            doc1: freq=3, positions=[11,33,45],\n            doc3: freq=1, positions=[21],\n            }\n    “slow” -> {\n            doc1: freq=1, positions=[12],\n            }\n    ","locked":false,"version":991,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"aN","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"### Indexing Flow\n\n- Index service consumes “crawl.parsed” events from the message queue.\n  {url, documentId}\n\n- The indexer retrieves the document content from the database.\n- It then breaks the content down into tokens (individual words).\n- Removes punctuations. Replaces & with “and” etc.\n- Converts all tokens\/words into lowercase.\n- Removes stop words such as “the”, “a”, “is”, “and”.\n- The reduces tokens into root forms. Knowns as Stemming\/Lemmatization.\n  For example\n    running, ran, runs -> run\n\n- Then it creates a map of word to freq and positions in local.\n  { \n    run: freq=3, positions=[11,33,45],\n    slow: freq=1, positions=[12],\n  }\n- Then it updates this document frequences in the index.\n   “run” -> {\n            doc1: freq=3, positions=[11,33,45],\n            doc3: freq=1, positions=[21],\n            }\n    “slow” -> {\n            doc1: freq=1, positions=[12],\n            }\n    ","height":700,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":49665860,"lineHeight":1.25,"fontFamily":8,"textAlign":"left","frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"angle":0,"x":308.15928386963196,"y":1166.3768354796694,"width":781},{"isDeleted":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"y9tee8PUbdupkhBrh4Nfk","strokeWidth":2,"seed":956365583,"roughness":1,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772622641651,"text":"### Search Service Flow\n\n- User submits a search query from front end app.\n- Search Service receives the query and applies the exact same text processing and analysis\n  steps used during indexing.\n    - tokenizaiton\n    - lowercasing\n    - normalization (punctuation removal)\n    - stop word removal\n    - stemming\n\n- Then processed query tokens are looked up in the inverted index.\n- Retrieves documents ids associated with each token.\n“run” -> {doc1, doc3}\n“slow” -> {doc1}\n\n- Then these documents are ranked using some algorithm (Term Frequency- Inverse Document Frequency).\n- TF - How often term appears in the document. The more the count the more the relavance.\n- IDF - How Unique a term is across all the documents fetched. terms slow is more valuable than term “how”.\n\n- Then it aggregates and ranks the response and returns to the user.\n","locked":false,"version":933,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"aO","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"### Search Service Flow\n\n- User submits a search query from front end app.\n- Search Service receives the query and applies the exact same text processing and analysis\n  steps used during indexing.\n    - tokenizaiton\n    - lowercasing\n    - normalization (punctuation removal)\n    - stop word removal\n    - stemming\n\n- Then processed query tokens are looked up in the inverted index.\n- Retrieves documents ids associated with each token.\n“run” -> {doc1, doc3}\n“slow” -> {doc1}\n\n- Then these documents are ranked using some algorithm (Term Frequency- Inverse Document Frequency).\n- TF - How often term appears in the document. The more the count the more the relavance.\n- IDF - How Unique a term is across all the documents fetched. terms slow is more valuable than term “how”.\n\n- Then it aggregates and ranks the response and returns to the user.\n","height":550,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":828976892,"lineHeight":1.25,"fontFamily":8,"textAlign":"left","frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"angle":0,"x":314.15928386963196,"y":2021.4930464171694,"width":1177}],"version":2,"type":"excalidraw","appState":{"shouldCacheIgnoreZoom":false,"exportScale":2,"defaultSidebarDockedPreference":false,"openMenu":null,"showWelcomeScreen":true,"currentItemStrokeColor":"#1e1e1e","bindMode":"orbit","exportWithDarkMode":false,"lockedMultiSelections":{},"currentItemRoughness":1,"currentItemTextAlign":"left","exportBackground":true,"scrolledOutside":true,"selectedElementIds":{},"zenModeEnabled":false,"currentItemStartArrowhead":null,"zoom":{"value":0.25593500000000002},"theme":"light","activeTool":{"locked":false,"fromSelection":false,"lastActiveTool":null,"type":"selection","customType":null},"exportEmbedScene":false,"gridStep":5,"lastPointerDownWith":"mouse","selectedGroupIds":{},"currentItemBackgroundColor":"transparent","scrollY":3885.1694638573349,"penDetected":false,"viewBackgroundColor":"#ffffff","name":"Untitled-2026-03-04-1220","currentItemFontFamily":5,"currentItemArrowType":"round","currentItemOpacity":100,"preferredSelectionTool":{"type":"selection","initialized":true},"scrollX":5449.0049890778582,"stats":{"open":false,"panels":3},"objectsSnapModeEnabled":false,"gridSize":20,"gridModeEnabled":false,"openSidebar":null,"currentItemRoundness":"round","currentItemStrokeStyle":"solid","editingGroupId":null,"previousSelectedElementIds":{},"currentChartType":"bar","currentItemStrokeWidth":2,"cursorButton":"up","currentItemEndArrowhead":"arrow","currentItemFillStyle":"solid","currentItemFontSize":20,"selectedLinearElement":null,"penMode":false},"source":"https:\/\/excalidraw.com","files":{}}